billedcost.short_description: Represents the actual cost billed for the Azure resource usage.
billedcost.long_description: This column contains the cost in a floating-point number format, reflecting the finalized cost after discounts and adjustments. The value range is from 0.0 to 992.32695, indicating the cost can be zero or a positive value. It's likely in the currency specified by 'billingcurrency'.

billingaccountid.short_description: Unique identifier for the billing account associated with the Azure usage.
billingaccountid.long_description: This column stores the billing account ID as an object (likely a string). All entries have the same value, indicating all usage is associated with a single billing account. The string is 53 characters long and consists of alphanumeric characters.

billingaccountname.short_description: The name of the billing account associated with the Azure usage.
billingaccountname.long_description: This column contains the name of the billing account. All entries have the same value, suggesting usage data pertains to a single billing account. The name is a string of 17 characters.

billingaccounttype.long_description: This column indicates the type of the billing account. All rows have the same value, the column contains a string of 15 characters, indicating a consistent billing account type for the data set.

billingcurrency.short_description: The currency in which the costs are billed.
billingcurrency.long_description: This column specifies the currency used for billing. The column contains only one distinct value and it's a 3-character string, likely representing a standard currency code (e.g., USD, EUR). The value is expected to be consistent across all rows, indicating all costs are in the same currency.

billingperiodend.short_description: The end date of the billing period.
billingperiodend.long_description: Indicates the end date for the billing cycle. The format is a string of 23 characters. There are three distinct values, suggesting the data spans three different billing cycles. The format is probably a datetime string.

billingperiodstart.short_description: The start date of the billing period.
billingperiodstart.long_description: Specifies the start date of the billing cycle. The format is a string of 23 characters. There are three distinct values, corresponding to the start dates of the billing cycles. The format is probably a datetime string.

chargecategory.long_description: This column classifies the type of charge, which is likely related to services, products, or discounts. The column contains two distinct string values (e.g., 'Discount', 'Usage') with lengths between 5 and 8 characters. The values are expected to be all letters.

chargeperiodstart.short_description: The start date of the charge period.
chargeperiodstart.long_description: This indicates the start date of the specific period for which the charge applies. The format is a string of 23 characters. There are 92 distinct values, suggesting a more granular time frame than billing periods.

commitmentdiscountstatus.long_description: Indicates the status of the commitment discount, such as 'Active', 'Inactive', or 'Pending'. The values are strings of 4-7 characters. The values are expected to be all letters.

consumedquantity.short_description: The quantity of the resource consumed.
consumedquantity.long_description: The amount of a resource used, in a numerical format. The values are floating-point numbers. The column has a value range from 0.0 to a very high number, indicating a wide range of consumption values.

consumedunit.short_description: The unit of measurement for the consumed quantity.
consumedunit.long_description: The unit of measurement associated with the 'consumedquantity' (e.g., GB, hours, units). The column contains 13 distinct string values, and lengths are between 2 and 11 characters. The values are mostly all letters.

contractedcost.long_description: The contracted cost, likely a cost derived from a contract or a commitment. The values are floating-point numbers. The value range is from 0.0 to 992.32695.

effectivecost.short_description: The effective cost after any discounts or adjustments.
effectivecost.long_description: The cost of the resource usage after applying any commitment discounts or other reductions. The values are floating-point numbers.  The range is from 0.0 to 992.32695.

invoiceissuername.short_description: The name of the invoice issuer.

listcost.short_description: The list price before any discounts are applied.

listunitprice.short_description: The unit price of the resource, before discounts.
